# Contributing to {{ project_name }}

## General setup

Start with the [general setup instructions](../setup/index.md) so that you can successfully run

```bash
conda activate {{ package_name }}-py312-workflow
snakemake conda_localize
```

## Create development conda environments

The following command will create named conda environments to help you with development.

```bash
conda activate {{ package_name }}-py312-workflow
snakemake --cores 1 conda_update
```

Most development tasks can occur in the `{{ package_name }}-py312-dev-runner` environment since this has the `runner` extras and most of the dependency groups installed. See `project.toml` for more information on the installed dependencies. (The environment YAML files found in the `workflow/envs/` directory are generated by the `pyproject2conda` and `conda_localize` rules from the dependencies specified in the `pyproejct.toml` file.)

## Configure VSCode

Follow the [VSCode setup instructions](vscode.md) to create an effective development environment.
